Overview

The dashboard offers a comprehensive view of several different quality measures such as:

  • Visits per Half Day

  • UDS Composite Score

  • Patient Satisfaction Surveys Score

  • Continuity of Care Score

1 - Patients Seen

The \(\#\) of patients seen, or in other words, the \(\#\) of completed billable patient encounters.

Medical Directors Only

Visit Statistics Dashboard.

Providers

At this time providers do not have access to the Visit Statistics Dashboard.

2 - Patients Surveyed

The \(\#\) of patients who have completed a survey after their visit.

For more information please see section 5 - Patient Satisfaction Surveys

Update Frequency

The report is typically updated the \(2nd\) week of every month for the prior months data.

4 - UDS Composite Score

Family Medicine \ Internal Medicine serves different patient populations compared to Pediatrics. Thus, it is appropriate to use quality measures that apply to these respective departments.

The quality measures are then aggregated into a single composite score.

Family Medicine & Internal Medicine Measures

\(1.\) Breast Cancer Screening \(7.\) HIV Screening
\(2.\) Cervical Cancer Screening \(8\) Statin Therapy
\(3.\) Colo-rectal Cancer Screening \(9.\) Tobacco Screening & Cessation
\(4.\) Controlling High Blood Pressure \(10.\) Use of Aspirin of Anti platelet
\(5.\) Depression Screening \(11.\) Weight Assessment & Counseling
\(6.\) Diabetes: Hemoglobin A1c

Pediatric Measures

\(1.\) Childhood Immunizations \(3.\) Depression Screening & Follow Up
\(2.\) Depression Remission \(4.\) Weight Assessment & Counseling
Medical Directors & Indivual Providers

UDS Report.

5 - Patient Satisfaction Surveys

6 - Continuity of Care

Continuity is calculated as a percentage \((\%)\) from the following formula:

Â 

\[\frac{\# \space \space of \space Visits \space \space with \space \space Assigned \space \space Patients }{\# \space \space Completed \space \space Visits}= Continuity \space \space \%\]

Â 

Medical Directors & Indivual Providers

Continuity Report.

Note

If you have any continuity or empanelment questions contact Sara Ruiz.

7 - Weighted Score

Each measure is assigned a weight, these weights can be found below:

Measures Weight
Half Day Score \(40\%\)
UDS Composite Score \(30\%\)
Patient Surveys Score \(20\%\)
Continuity of Care \(10\%\)
TOTAL \(100\%\)

Weighted Score Example

Measure Weight Score Weighted Score
Half Day Score \(40\%\) \(\times\) \(99\%\) \(=\) \(0.396\)
UDS Composite Score \(30\%\) \(\times\) \(71.1\%\) \(=\) \(0.2133\)
Patient Surveys Score \(20\%\) \(\times\) \(97\%\) \(=\) \(0.194\)
Continuity of Care \(10\%\) \(\times\) \(95\%\) \(=\) \(0.095\)
Weighted Score Total \(0.8983 \approx 90.0\%\)

Drill Down Information

To view the data behind the individual scores follow these steps:

  1. Click anywhere on your row of information.

  2. A pop-up menu will appear with links to each of the individual reports.

Accessing the Report

In order to view the report on Tableau you must be on a SAC Health OR Loma Linda University Health internet connection either by being at one of the sites or via VPN.

Once logged into Tableau you can find the report with the following steps:

  1. Open the Clinical folder.

  2. Click on Individual Provider Dashboard.

  3. Select Individual Provider View.

Note

Clicking the star symbol next to the name of the report will add it to your favorites section located on the left side of the screen.
